= Introduction

This project targets an off-device monocular VSLAM benchmark for smartphone video with unknown
intrinsics. The main goal is to compare modern dense monocular systems, recover camera trajectories
with limited calibration assumptions, and evaluate dense reconstructions under a common protocol.

The benchmark centers on two output surfaces: trajectory quality and dense 3D point cloud quality.
In addition to method accuracy, the project tracks runtime and memory requirements because the final
recommendation must balance precision, robustness, and practical execution cost.
